title: Dowland - Third Book of Songs - Kirkby, et al
description:
John Dowland: The Third Book of Songs, 1603.

Here are twenty-one songs, published by Dowland in 1603, performed perfectly by the Consort of Musicke, under the direction of Anthony Rooley (lute). The recording was originally released by L'Oiseau-Lyre in 1977. The vocalists on this recording are as follows:

Emma Kirkby, soprano
John York Skinner, counter-tenor
Martyn Hill, tenor
David Thomas, bass

Please enjoy.
